---------------
Gob Online Chat - Change Log
---------------

============
Version: 0.4
Date: 2004/02

Features

- Added full UniCode support (see sf #872999)
- Added Windows Installation instructions (see sf #888024)
- Added Windows Installation application (see sf #830899)
- Windows Service support for server.jar (see sf #830890)
- Applet Window Resizing (see sf #830892)
- Put in new Ant targets for building Windows Packaging (.exe)
- Put in new Ant targets for building Tarball packaging (.tar.gz)
- Added a thick client for testing - still a little buggy
- Keepalive support now provided with regular pings and timeouts (see sf 
#831429)
- Room list helpers, including auto focusing on primary text fields (see sf 
#831685)
- Auto-restart upon exception (see sf #889516)

Bug Fixes

- Server Crash: ArrayIndexOutOfBounds exception (see sf #879745)
- Server Crash: ClassCastException. No handling of invalid XML objects (see sf #889512)

============
Version: 0.3
Date: 2004/01/19

Features

- A progress bar is now presented while the applet is loading
- Re-arranged Package Name under sh.bob.gob  (see sf #830410)
- Created Common Regex Libs and utilised them in ClientCommand (see sf #830411)
- Server Configuration File (see sf #830828)
- Debugging and Logging Runtime Configuration (see sf #830832)
- XML Protocol Sub-system (see sf #830375)
- Compressed protocol for speed
- I dabbled in some colour changes

Bug fixes

- A UserList bug was fixed by the change to XML

============
Version: 0.2
Date: 2003/10/25

Features

- Java Applet is now started in its own HTML window (see sf #688359)
- The lobby is now removed while disconnected (see sf #686540)
- Added support for user renaming (see sf #686542)
- Added support for private chat (see sf #688367)
- Added support for rooms (see sf #688363)
- Gob now loads "panels" for each tab, allowing a more modular configuration.
- There is a seperate Runnable class for the thread. 
- Documentation Updated.
- Server port is now set on the command line.

Bug fixes

- Fixed handling of failed connections, signups and selector registration. 
Now you don't need to hit disconnect yourself (see sf #686534).
- Will now handle the characters []\ in a message.

============